  "local_port": 57116,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much does an average self publishing author make on Amazon?",
  "response": "The income of an average self-published author on Amazon varies widely and depends on several factors, such as the number of books published, genre, pricing, marketing efforts, and the author's ability to build an audience. Here\u2019s a breakdown of what to expect:\n\n### Key Factors Affecting Earnings:\n1. **Royalties**:  \n   - Amazon offers **35% or 70% royalties**, depending on the price and format of the book.  \n   - eBooks priced between **$2.99 and $9.99** typically earn a 70% royalty.  \n   - Paperback and hardcover royalties are lower, usually around **60%** of the list price minus printing costs.\n\n2. **Book Sales Volume**:  \n   - Many self-published authors sell **fewer than 100 copies** of a book.  \n   - A small percentage of authors sell **thousands of copies**, especially those with strong marketing strategies or a series of books.\n\n3. **Genre**:  \n   - Some genres, like romance, mystery, and science fiction, tend to sell better than others.  \n   - Non-fiction authors in niche markets can also do well if they target a specific audience.\n\n4. **Marketing and Promotion**:  \n   - Authors who actively promote their books through social media, email lists, and paid ads tend to earn more.  \n   - Without marketing, most books struggle to gain visibility.\n\n### Average Earnings:\n- **Most self-published authors earn less than $1,000 per year** from their books.  \n- According to surveys and industry reports (e.g., from **Author Earnings** or **ALLi**), the **median annual income** for self-published authors is around **$1,000\u2013$3,000**.  \n- A small percentage of authors (often those with multiple books or a strong following) earn **$10,000 or more** per year.  \n\n### Success Stories:\n- Rarely, authors achieve substantial success, earning **six figures or more** annually. These authors often reinvest heavily in marketing, publish frequently, and build a loyal readership.\n\n### Tips to Increase Earnings:\n1. **Publish Multiple Books**: Authors with several books tend to earn more, as each book helps promote the others.  \n2. **Optimize Pricing**: Price eBooks within the $2.99\u2013$9.99 range to maximize royalties.  \n3. **Invest in Marketing**: Use platforms like Facebook Ads, Amazon Ads, and email marketing to reach readers.  \n4. **Focus on Covers and Blurbs**: A professional cover and compelling description can significantly boost sales.  \n5. **Engage with Readers**: Build a community through social media or a mailing list to keep readers coming back.\n\nIn summary, while the average self-published author on Amazon makes modest earnings, success is achievable with strategic planning, persistence, and effective marketing.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
